</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,434,566]" pageId="17" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName box="[189,342,434,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,342,434,460]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="17">Smeringopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently the most species-rich African pholcid genus, but only two species occur in West Africa (
<figureCitation box="[348,438,469,495]" captionStart="Figs 33 - 34" captionStartId="18.[189,241,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[192,1395,544,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1396,544,1924]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 33 - 34. Known distributions of the genera Smeringopus Simon, 1890 and Spermophora Hentz, 1841 in West Africa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406606/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="17">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
): the pantropical synanthropic 
<taxonomicName authority="Blackwall, 1858" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1858" box="[809,1158,469,496]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[809,935,469,495]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="17">S. pallidus</emphasis>
(Blackwall, 1858)
</taxonomicName>
and the widespread Guineo-Congolian 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1907" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1907" box="[413,783,504,531]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrogaster">
<emphasis box="[413,610,504,531]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="17">S. cylindrogaster</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon E." box="[624,775,504,530]" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale di Genova" pageId="17" pageNumber="17" pagination="218 - 323" part="43" refString="Simon E. 1907. Arachnides recueillis par L. Fea sur la cote occidentale d'Afrique. Annali del Museo civico di storia naturale di Genova 43: 218 - 323." title="Arachnides recueillis par L. Fea sur la cote occidentale d'Afrique" type="journal article" year="1907">Simon, 1907</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
which covers the entire Guineo-Congolian rainforest (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber B. A." box="[197,343,539,566]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="17" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 138" part="3461" refString="Huber B. A. 2012. Revision and cladistic analysis of the Afrotropical endemic genus Smeringopus Simon, 1890 (Araneae: Pholcidae). Zootaxa 3461: 1 - 138." title="Revision and cladistic analysis of the Afrotropical endemic genus Smeringopus Simon, 1890 (Araneae: Pholcidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Huber 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
